You are given four inputs:
A string representing your name.
An integer representing the number of Instagram followers.
An integer representing the number of posts youâ€™ve made.
A float representing the number of hours you use Instagram daily.
Input Format

The first line contains a string name.
The second line contains an integer followers.
The third line contains an integer posts.
The fourth line contains a float hours.
Constraints

1 <= length of name <= 100
0 <= followers <= 10^6
0 <= posts <= 10^5
0.0 <= hours <= 24.0
Output Format

My name is , my Instagram has followers, I have posted posts, and I use Instagram for hours daily.

Sample Input 0

Boss  
1000  
80  
3.5
Sample Output 0

My name is Boss, my Instagram has 1000 followers, I have posted 80 posts, and I use Instagram for 3.5 hours daily.

Code

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        String name=sc.nextLine().trim();
        int followers=sc.nextInt();
        int post=sc.nextInt();
        float hours=sc.nextFloat();
        
        System.out.println("My name is "+name+", my Instagram has "+followers+" followers, I have posted "+post+" posts, and I use Instagram for "+hours+" hours daily.");
        
    }
}
